JOHANNESBURG – Old Mutual Plc has officially unbundled the group. Old Mutual Limited made its debut on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange and the London Stock Exchange and in selected African countries. Listed, our proudest moment ever @JSE_Group #JSE #WithAfricaForAfrica pic.twitter.com/4nD78OYYBC The listing is part of the group's separation strategy, which was announced in March 2016. READ: Old Mutual closer to buying UK-based unit The plan is to separate the London-based group into four independent, standalone companies. The company’s CEO says this will enable it to unlock shareholder value. And create a business with a strong strategic focus on sub-Saharan Africa. Old mutual has assured consumers that the day-to-day running of the business will continue as usual. eNCA